            <p>S. MORAIS&#44;<lb/>
                546 N. FIFTH STREET.<lb/></p>
            <p>Philadelphia&#44; December 2<hi rend="sup">nd</hi> 1889<lb/></p>
            <p>Professor Dr Richard Gottheil<lb/>
                My Dear Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>From all I can gather&#44; the author<lb/> about whom you make inquiries&#44; was called<lb/> Rav&#225;.  Possibly&#44; his family name was<lb/> &#91;Hebrew&#93; with an &#91;Hebrew&#93;&#44; and as Jews of the Italian<lb/> school&#44; like those of the Ashkenazie&#44; give the<lb/> &#91;Hebrew&#93; without Dagesh a soft sound&#44; he may<lb/> have gone by the name of Rav&#225; and not<lb/> Rabb&#225;&#44; as you spell it&#44;&#45;&#45;I <del>know</del> remember a number<lb/> of families in Italy called Rav&#225;.  You are<lb/> perfectly aware that in the Talmud we have<lb/> both &#91;Hebrew&#93; and &#91;Hebrew&#93;.<lb/></p>
            <p>It seems that our author lived and taught<lb/> in Padua&#44; not in Modena&#44; as Wolff sug&#45;<lb/>&#45;gests.  It was by the advice of Rabbi<lb/> Azariah de Fano&#44; whose intimate acquaintance<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>he enjoyed&#44; that he published the posthumous<lb/> work of his father&#44; entitled &#91;Hebrew&#93; before<lb/> any other.<lb/></p>
            <p>Elizzah ben Menachem Rav&#225; is said to<lb/> have written &#91;Hebrew&#93;&#45;&#45;an enlargement and<lb/> complement of the fourth part of his father&#39;s<lb/> &#91;Hebrew&#93; &#40;I do not meet with the book<lb/> &#91;Hebrew&#93; among his writings.  A work bear&#45;<lb/>ing that title&#44; I find ascribed <del>belonging</del> to Issachar<lb/> Entenburg&#41;<lb/></p>
            <p>The above information is derived from<lb/> a catalogue of manuscripts prepared by my<lb/> venerable and <del>venerated</del> greatly esteemed friend Marco Mortara&#44;<lb/> chief Rabbi of Manuta&#44; the Nestor of the<lb/> modern Rabbinate in Italy.<lb/></p>
            <p>I shall feel grateful&#44; in case you make<lb/> public use of the information&#44; if you will<lb/> give him full credit.<lb/>  Yours truly<lb/> S Morais<lb/></p>
            <p>&#43; Catalogo Die Manoscritti Ebraici&#44; Della Bibliotheca<lb/> della Communita Israelitica Di Mantova&#44; Compilato dal<lb/> Rabbino Maggiore Marco Mortara Livorno Tipografia<lb/> I. Costa &#38; Co. 1878<lb/></p>
